## Users API

**Base URL:** <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/user \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### Get Current User

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/user" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Response fields:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `id` | User ID |
| `username` | Username |
| `name` | Display name |
| `email` | Email address |
| `state` | Account state: `active`, `blocked`, or `banned` |
| `locked` | Whether the account is locked |
| `admin` | Whether the user has admin privileges |
| `created_at` | Account creation timestamp |
| `confirmed_at` | Email confirmation timestamp |
| `last_sign_in_at` | Last sign-in timestamp |
| `current_sign_in_at` | Current session sign-in timestamp |
| `web_url` | Profile URL |

**Example response:**

```json
{
  "id": 1,
  "username": "john_smith",
  "name": "John Smith",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "state": "active",
  "locked": false,
  "admin": false,
  "created_at": "2024-01-15T08:00:58Z",
  "confirmed_at": "2024-01-15T09:05:22Z",
  "last_sign_in_at": "2024-06-01T11:41:01Z",
  "current_sign_in_at": "2024-06-02T06:36:55Z",
  "web_url": "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/john_smith"
}
```

---

### List Users (admin only)

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Filter by username:

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users?username=john_smith" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters** (all optional):

| Parameter | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `username` | Filter by exact username |

**Example response:**

```json
[
  { "id": 1, "username": "john_smith", "name": "John Smith", "email": "john@example.com" },
  { "id": 2, "username": "jane_doe", "name": "Jane Doe", "email": "jane@example.com" }
]
```

---

### Create a User (admin only)

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "email": "newuser@example.com",
    "name": "New User",
    "username": "newuser",
    "password": "SecurePassword123!",
    "admin": false
  }'
```

**Request parameters:**

| Parameter | Required | Description |
|-----------|----------|-------------|
| `email` | yes | Email address of the new user |
| `name` | yes | Display name |
| `username` | yes | Username (must be unique) |
| `password` | yes | Account password |
| `admin` | no | Set to `true` to grant admin privileges (default: `false`) |

**Response fields:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `id` | User ID |
| `username` | Username |
| `name` | Display name |
| `email` | Email address |
| `state` | Account state |
| `admin` | Whether the user has admin privileges |
| `created_at` | Account creation timestamp |
| `confirmed_at` | Email confirmation timestamp (auto-confirmed for admin-created accounts) |
| `web_url` | Profile URL |

**Example response:**

```json
{
  "id": 42,
  "username": "newuser",
  "name": "New User",
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "state": "active",
  "admin": false,
  "created_at": "2024-06-01T08:00:00Z",
  "confirmed_at": "2024-06-01T08:00:00Z",
  "web_url": "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/newuser"
}
```

---

### Get a User by ID (admin only)

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users/:id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Returns the same fields as the create response.

---

### Update a User (admin only)

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users/:id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name": "Updated Name", "admin": true}'
```

**Request parameters** (all optional):

| Parameter | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `email` | New email address |
| `name` | New display name |
| `username` | New username |
| `password` | New password |
| `admin` | Grant or revoke admin privileges |

Returns the updated user fields on success.

---

### Block a User (admin only)

Blocks a user so they can no longer sign in, use the API, or access git. Their existing
data and contributions are preserved. This is the reversible alternative to deletion.

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users/:id/block" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Returns `204 No Content` on success. The user's `state` becomes `blocked`.

---

### Unblock a User (admin only)

Reactivates a blocked user. Their `state` returns to `active` and they can sign in again.

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users/:id/unblock" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Returns `204 No Content` on success.

---

### Delete a User (admin only)

> **Not implemented.** User deletion is not available. Block the user instead (see above).
> This endpoint returns `501 Not Implemented`.

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/users/:id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```
